snippet.textDisplay:
While I appreciate the sentiment about pre-ordering I have to disagree. While I completely agree when it comes to games and other DIGITAL goods, when it comes to physical goods, I feel that pre-ordering is justified. Where digital goods don't have a limited stock and they don't require time to produce more copies of the good, physical goods do have a limited stock and take time to produce. 


TL;DR You can get a digital good right after it's released, but you could end up waiting months after release for a physical good without a pre-order.
